{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646402","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646402"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:30:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:30:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18180"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18180","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18180"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10894"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80688"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10894","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10894"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18180"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65986"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7166"},{"type":"tags","id":"7178"},{"type":"tags","id":"11415"},{"type":"tags","id":"11416"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25333"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25336"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80688","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80688"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe autonomic nervous system involves various components, including the dorsal and ventral rami, as well as the white and gray rami communicans. These structures have specific roles in the distribution of nerve signals.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following correctly matches the function of these structures?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["White rami communicans: output from sympathetic chain to target tissue; gray rami communicans: output from spinal cord to sympathetic chain","Gray rami communicans: output from spinal cord to sympathetic chain; white rami communicans: output from sympathetic chain to target tissue","Dorsal rami: supply intrinsic muscles of the back; ventral rami: supply the rest of the body","Dorsal rami: supply the rest of the body; ventral rami: supply intrinsic muscles of the back","Ventral rami: supply intrinsic muscles of the back; dorsal rami: supply the rest of the body"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct match is \u003Cstrong\u003Edorsal rami: supply intrinsic muscles of the back; ventral rami: supply the rest of the body\u003C/strong\u003E. Dorsal rami innervate the intrinsic muscles of the back and the overlying skin, while ventral rami supply the rest of the body, often forming nerve plexuses.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVentral rami: supply intrinsic muscles of the back\u003C/strong\u003E - Ventral rami do not supply the intrinsic muscles of the back\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWhite rami communicans: output from sympathetic chain to target tissue\u003C/strong\u003E - White rami communicans carry signals from the spinal cord to the sympathetic chain\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGray rami communicans: output from spinal cord to sympathetic chain\u003C/strong\u003E - Gray rami communicans carry signals from the sympathetic chain to target tissues\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal rami: supply the rest of the body\u003C/strong\u003E - Dorsal rami do not supply the rest of the body\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Dorsal rami supply the intrinsic muscles of the back and the overlying skin.","Ventral rami supply the rest of the body, often after merging with other ventral rami via a nerve plexus.","White rami communicans carry output from the spinal cord to the sympathetic chain.","Gray rami communicans carry output from the sympathetic chain to target tissues."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Henson B, Kadiyala B, Edens MA. Anatomy, Back, Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537074/","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","DeSai C, Reddy V, Agarwal A. Anatomy, Back, Vertebral Column. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK525969/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65986"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18180"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65986"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-22T11:29:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-22T11:30:34+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10894"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80688"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable